commit.message: Fix -S option to search description and name as documented
Convert from tabs to PEP8 4 spaces for indentation

Fix python 3 compatability with 'esearch -e' (Bug 469076)

Thanks to zmedico for the patch.

Fix setup.py so that either VERSION or PVR will set the version.

This fixes the issue with egg-info always having a version number of
9999.  Fix is from Brian Dolbec courtesy of mirrorselect.
fix a redefinition of error, unify all 3 copies
split SyntaxError exception away to raise the error.
make the db unicode and correctly imported by both py2 and p3

Merge branch 'pu/exclude'

This resolves https://bugs.gentoo.org/show_bug.cgi?id=195481
Modified filter_excluded() to use the python builtin filter().

Updated doc with the new --exclude switch.

TODO: Update of french and italian man pages

Added -x/--exclude option.

When using this option (with an regex as argument), those hits matching
the exclude pattern will we suppressed in the output.

If an --exclude pattern was specified, filter_excluded() is called after
search_list() and before output_results(). It iterates over all packages
search_list() has found, and drops those which match the --exclude
pattern.

Multiple --exclude patterns are also possible, all packages matching at
least one of them will be dropped from the search result.

squash! Added

Broke up create_regexp() into smaller parts.

The functionality of create_regexp() is now divided into two smaller
functions, create_regex() and create_regexlist().
The former just creates a regex from a pattern string, while the latter
arranges this output in a regexlist data structure.

This was done for refactoring; I'll later need the bare functionality of
create_regex().

Merge pull request #4 from atlaua/master

Bug: Undefined variable in sync()

Use of undefined variable in sync()

The variable 'warnings' in sync() is undefined if esync is called
without --layman-sync. This causes esync to fail when executing the
'if warnings ...' statement.
Reprint warnings detected during layman sync API operations at the end of the sync output.
Fix log file name printed in error message for layman sync errors.

Use relative paths for man page installations.

Fixes bug where EPREFIX=''(the default), causes man pages to be installed in to
/usr/usr/share/man due to non-anchored paths.

Signed-off-by: Paul Varner <fuzzyray@gentoo.org>

Merge pull request #3 from atlaua/master

Python3-fix in update.py

Fixed an incompability with python3 in getfetchsize()

The /-operator of python3 now uses float divison even if the inputs are integers, so we have to explicitly state that we want to use integer divison by using // instead of /. This change is compatible to python2.

Merge pull request #2 from atlaua/master

Update to sync.py for python3 support

Updated sync.py for python3 support.

The syntax of sort has changed in py3, now you don't specify a (lambda) function for comparing two items, but a sort key. The change is compatible with python2.

Use floor division in the duration function.

Without using floor division we can end up with outout like:
esearch-index generated in 1.2333333333333334 minute(s) and 14 second(s)
Commit French translation updates thanks to Fab, bug 396111.
Fix setup.py to work with EPREFIX changes in Portage.
apply zmedico's patch to fix EPREFIX capability.
Update Itilian man pages courtesy of Maurizio Camisaschi.  Also fix a missing '-' for the -s option.
change my email address
add missing -N option to esearch manpage and add missing -h option to esearch.parseopts()
